cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is about accelerating convolutional neural networks (CNNs) using depthwise separable convolutions, which is a popular technique in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves transfer learning and network optimization, which are common topics in machine learning, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a training-free method, which falls under the category of optimization and algorithm design, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. Finally, the paper applies the proposed method to object detection, which is a subfield of natural language processing, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a less likely but still possible category.
